d its status mirrors the latest preflight."],[1202,"Drive it over HTTP: API guide"],[901,"Dry-run preflight: `ready` / `needs_input` / `blocked`, nothing created"],[151,"Durable configured views over work items — the software-factory surfaces that workflows keep up to date."],[1014,"Each card takes one of three decisions:"],[26,"Each deployment serves its own CLI install script:"],[677,"Each item also carries `type` (`feature`, `bug`, `research`, `release`, `maintenance`, `idea`), `priority` (`urgent`, `high`, `normal`, `low`), `project`, `owner`/`requester`, `acceptanceCriteria`, `nextAction`, `blockedReason`, and an optional `dueAt`."],[1059,"Each pending card is posted as a message carrying the ask (what approving does, why a human is needed), a sanitized input summary, and inline buttons: **Approve**, **Request changes**, **Reject**. Only the configured approval user ids can act; a button press resolves the card exactly like the web or API would, and the message is edited to show the resolution (\"Approved by ... at ...\") with the buttons removed."],[251,"Each profile has a fixed `kind` with a fixed set of config keys — anything else is rejected, so raw credentials or ad-hoc shell fragments can never be smuggled into a profile:"],[382,"Each runner declares a `capacity` (concurrent run slots) and reports its active runs; the Hub assigns work only to free slots. `GET /api/runners` returns every registered runner with heartbeat state, capacity, active slots, plus a pool summary — the same data the **Runners** page in the web app shows (`#runners`)."],[505,"Each schedule tracks `nextRunAt`, `lastRunAt`, the last run id, and the last fire status, all visible on the Schedules page (`#schedules`) and in the API."],[228,"Edit the workflow (admin)."],[253,"Effect"],[495,"Enable, disable, run now"],[723,"Enabled and disabled"],[932,"Encrypted secrets store — names and metadata only, never values (admin)"],[59,"Endpoint"],[128,"Endpoint"],[181,"Endpoint"],[284,"Endpoint"]