ult branch stays behind explicit run promotion."],[801,"Push instead of poll: response endpoints"],[1285,"Pushed `v*` tags"],[1288,"Pushed `v*` tags"],[516,"Query: `cron`, `timezone`."],[1112,"Quick install (host bootstrap)"],[11,"Quickstart"],[842,"Rate limits"],[657,"Raw ask, idea, bug, or product need."],[964,"Re-preflight and enqueue the real run only when ready — `202` with `{run, draft}`"],[1387,"Re-run; if recurring, raise the workflow's time budget or shrink the job."],[1378,"Read the run logs for the gate output; fix the underlying work and re-run."],[1396,"Read the run output and the linked approval/escalation card."],[57,"Reading any catalog requires only an authenticated token. Creating and updating entries requires the `admin` scope — the catalogs are part of the Hub's trusted configuration, like secrets and hook profiles."],[1101,"Reads available to any token: `runyard runners` (runner pool), `runyard agents`,\n`runyard skills`, `runyard knowledge -q <query>`, `runyard hooks [--workflow <slug>]`, and `runyard hook describe|validate <slug>`. Secrets have\nno CLI subcommand — manage them in the web UI, over the\nAPI (`PUT /api/secrets/:key`), or with the MCP `set_secret` tool."],[862,"Reads such as listing runs, workflows, or artifacts require any authenticated\ntoken. A token with only the `read` scope is therefore read-only: it can\ninspect everything non-admin but every create/update/delete/run/approve call\nfails with `403`. A request with no valid token gets\n`401 {\"error\": \"unauthorized\"}`; a token missing a required scope gets:"],[589,"Reads such as listing runs, workflows, runners, or schedules need only an authenticated token, whatever its scopes. Runner lifecycle endpoints additionally enforce **run ownership**: only the runner token that claimed a run (or an admin) may report on it."],[421,"Ready for a matching runner to claim."],[1283,"Real bubblewrap + AppArmor gate on Ubuntu 24.04: installs bwrap, loads the repo's AppArmor profile via t