nresolved `engine.approval.waiting` parks its step in `waiting`; the run's own terminal status closes the books (succeeded finishes unfinished active steps, cancelled cancels them, a failure-terminal status fails the step the run died on). When no source graph exists the flow degrades to an event-derived stepper rather than hiding observed work. The ticket detail renders this as the flow view for the active or latest linked run."],[812,"The full HTTP surface, generated from the Hub's API surface registry — it cannot drift from the routes the server actually registers."],[1034,"The gated side effect is allowed to run."],[1274,"The GitHub Actions pipeline (`.github/workflows/release.yml` and `images.yml`) has four jobs:"],[1022,"The held run is released to the queue and executes."],[282,"The hook did not run."],[1043,"The Hub can post approval cards to a Telegram chat and accept decisions from the buttons on them."],[1157,"The Hub is a single HTTP listener; any TLS-terminating proxy that forwards **all\npaths** to the Hub port works. With Caddy:"],[1138,"The Hub listens on `127.0.0.1:43117` by default. Start a runner in a second\nprocess:"],[1128,"The Hub uses the built-in `node:sqlite` module (started with `--experimental-sqlite`)"],[818,"The live, private catalog: workflows with schemas, execution modes, runner pool state, and ready-to-use CLI/MCP invocations."],[366,"The machines that claim and execute runs via the Smithers engine - registration, tags, capacity, health, and sandboxing."],[409,"The needs-attention queue"],[1208,"The parity guarantee"],[1150,"The portable base stack is `docker-compose.yml` at the repo root:"],[501,"The preview returns a human-readable description plus the next fire instants — nothing is created."],[278,"The profile cannot execute — typically missing named secrets or a disabled secret store."],[280,"The profile was not eligible for this run."],[1270,"The release-train helper"],[1134,"The repository ships a one-command, idempotent bootstrap script for a fresh\nLinux box:"],[1140,"The repository ships generic units in `deploy/`. The Hub unit\n(`deploy/runyard.service`):"],[21,"The repository's install script is a one-command, idempotent bootstrap. It installs Node 22 and pnpm if needed, clones Runyard at the latest release tag (default `/opt/runyard`), generates an env file with a `SECRETS_ENC_KEY` and session secret, creates the data directory, and installs systemd units for the Hub and a runner:"],[1346,"The reusable secret store is enabled by setting `SECRETS_ENC_KEY` (a 32-byte key) on the Hub; without a valid key the feature is disabled rather than degraded. Values are encrypted at rest and are write-only from the API's point of view: `GET /api/secrets` returns names and metadata, never values, and secrets are redacted from API responses, events, approval cards, and audit entries. Workflows reference secrets by name; the Hub injects values into runs that declared them."],[1386,"The run exceeded a deadline or an operation timed out."],[546,"the run input's `input.secretNames` list."],[1024,"The run is cancelled — a human \"no\" is a decision, not a failure."],[1023,"The run is cancelled; your note tells the requester what to change."],[1371,"The run is held on an approval card, which is by design: approval-held runs are never failed or reaped for waiting. Find and resolve the card — web **Approvals**, `runyard approvals` then `runyard approve|reject|request-changes <approval-id>`, or the MCP tools. See Approvals."],[404,"The run lifecycle, preflight and run drafts, events and artifacts, reruns, and promotion."],[1139,"The runner authenticates with a runner-scoped token (`RUNYARD_HUB_TOKEN`); on a\nfresh Hub it may use the bootstrap token until you mint one."],[342,"The runner observes the terminal status on its next poll and cancels the detached engine run, and the gateway refuses further calls from that run's token (`403`)."],[402,"The runner protocol endpoints intentionally have no MCP tools